In this article, President Obama discusses the H1N1 flu virus outbreak and reassures Americans that the government is taking necessary precautions. He also mentions the steps taken to recover the economy, such as passing the Recovery Act, providing health insurance for children, and implementing a housing plan. The President emphasizes the need to build a new foundation for growth, with investments in education, renewable energy, healthcare, and deficit reduction. Despite progress, he acknowledges that more work needs to be done to address unemployment, housing, credit flow, and national security threats. He concludes by expressing confidence in rebuilding a stronger nation and remaining a symbol of opportunity for people around the world.